org.nuxeo.connect.update

Class Version

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.nuxeo.connect.update.Version
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<Version>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Version

    public class Version
extends Object
implements Comparable<Version>
    IMPORTANT: this file is copied from org.nuxeo.connect:nuxeo-connect-client:1.4.13 Those versions are used in the Marketplace packages. They are in the form major.minor.patch-classifier with some "special" classifiers which are "rc", "alpha", "beta" (upper or lower case), a letter followed by a date in the form AAAAMMDD (for instance "I20131022") and the SNAPSHOT classifier.
    Order is the following:
    x.y.z-beta
    x.y.z-r20131022
    x.y.z-SNAPSHOT
    x.y.z
    x.y.z-anyclassifier

    Classifiers are alphabetically ordered between themselves.
    Special classifiers are before the SNAPSHOT.
    SNAPSHOT is always just before the release (without classifier).
    Non-special classifiers are after the release.
    See TestVersions.
